        p.section-heading#s1 WHAT INFORMATION DOES PHWC COLLECT FROM ME?
        ol
          li
            u Information You Provide to Us
            | . When you visit the Site, we invite you to join our distribution list by providing your email in the “STAY IN TOUCH” field located at the bottom of the home page of our Site. Doing so is completely voluntary. We also provide an online form on our Site that allows you to send a message to PHWC by providing your name and e-mail address in the open text fields on the “CONTACT” page. Please know that if you contact us using the online form, or by email, we may keep a record of your contact information and correspondence, and may use your email address, and any information that you provide to us in your message, in order to respond to you. 
          li
            u Information We Collect About Your Interaction With The Site
            | . We may collect additional information about your interaction with the Site without identifying you as an individual (“
            strong Anonymous Information
            | ”), by using cookies or other technologies. For example, we may receive certain standard information that your browser sends to every website you visit, such as your IP address, browser and operating system type, and information about the device you are using (such as whether it is a mobile device or a desktop computer). We may use Anonymous Information for any purpose in our discretion. For clarity, Anonymous Information means information that is not associated with or linked to your personal information and does not permit the identification of individual persons.
        p.section-heading#s2 HOW IS INFORMATION COLLECTED BY PHWC USED AND SHARED?
        ol
          li
            u How We May Use Your Information
            | . We may use the information we collect from and about you through the Site for any of the following purposes: (i) to operate the Site and to provide products and services to you, (ii) to respond to your requests and inquiries, (iii) to contact you and to communicate with you in order to respond to your requests for additional information, (iv) to send you newsletters, alerts, and updates, (v) to notify you about important changes to the Site or our business, (vi) to review Site usage and operations and to improve the content and functionality of the Site, (vii) to protect the security or integrity of the Site or our business, (viii) to enforce our <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a>, or (ix) to tailor the Site to your needs and the needs of other visitors.
          li
            u How We May Share Your Information
            | . PHWC does not sell, lease or rent the personal information you share with us on or through the Site with third parties. PHWC may disclose your personal information to third parties only (i) as required by law or regulation or as we believe in good faith that disclosure of such personal information is reasonably necessary to: (1) satisfy any applicable law or regulation, (2) to respond to claims and/or to comply with a judicial proceeding, court order or legal process served on us, (3) to protect and defend our rights or property and/or the rights or property of third parties, as permitted by law, (4) to detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues; or (5) to enforce our <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a>; and/or (ii) with our service providers that provide certain services to maintain and operate the Site or to help us deliver services to you.
          li
            u Direct Marketing
            | . We may send out marketing communications (such as a newsletter) to our customers to update them about our products or developments with our business, to offer special promotions, or to announce upcoming events or important happenings in our industry. You can always choose to stop receiving newsletters or other communications from us by clicking the “unsubscribe” link at the bottom of a marketing message.
        p  
        p
          | As with any business, it is possible that in the future we could merge with or be acquired by another company. If this occurs, the successor company would have access to the Information, but would continue to be bound by this Privacy Policy unless and until it is amended.
        p  
        p.section-heading#s3 WILL PHWC SEND ME TEXT MESSAGES?
        p
          | At this time we will not send you notifications, alerts or other communications via text message.
        p  
        p.section-heading#s4 WHAT ELSE SHOULD I KNOW ABOUT ANONYMOUS INFORMATION COLLECTED BY PHWC?
        p
          | PHWC uses an analytics partner (“
          strong Analytics Partner
          | ”) to collect Anonymous Information about how our Site is used. Our Analytics Partner may use cookies, web beacons or other automated technologies to collect information about how many times you visit our Site, what parts of our Site you access, and what other websites you visit before and after visiting our Site. To help you understand these technologies better:
        ul
          li
            | “Cookies” are electronic files many websites place on a visitor’s computer to store information that makes each visit to a respective website more efficient. To remove cookies, you may configure your browser to clear all cookies, or configure it to reject cookies whenever you visit a new website.   Please consult your browser’s user guide for specific instructions on removing cookies.
          li
            | “Beacons” are small graphic files with a unique identifier that are used to track a web or mobile site user’s online movements. Unlike cookies, beacons are embedded on websites, not downloaded on your computer or device.
        p
          | Our Analytics Partner may use these or other techniques to collect Anonymous Information about your visit to our Site. In order to make sure you understand how our Analytics Partner handles your information and how it interacts with our Site, we’ve shared hyperlinks below to its Terms of Use. You should visit this page as PHWC has no ability to control or monitor our Analytics Partner’s data collection or data use practices.
        ul
          li
            u Google Analytics
            | — PHWC partners with Google Analytics to provide insight into our Site. Google Analytics’ terms are available here: 
            a(href='http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/us.html') http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/us.html
            | .
        p.section-heading#s5 HOW DOES PHWC PROTECT MY INFORMATION?
        p
          | PHWC uses reasonable administrative, physical and technical safeguards designed to secure the personal information you share with us. Regardless of the precautions taken by us or by you, no data transmitted over the Internet or any other public network can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. We cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us and you provide all personal information to us at your own risk.
        p.section-heading#s6 DOES PHWC COLLECT PAYMENT CARD INFORMATION?
        p
          | PHWC does not collect credit and debit card information directly through the Site and kindly asks you not to share this information with us when communicating with us by e-mail or submitting requests for additional information. PHWC does use a third-party credit card processor (“
          strong Payment Processor
          | ”) to process online transactions through our online store. Please note that your credit and debit card information (number, expiration date, security code) is provided directly to the Payment Processor and is stored by the Payment Processor and not by us, and as such, it is important to review the Payment Processor’s privacy policy and terms of service to understand their information security practices. The Payment Processor may share with us some of the information you submit in connection with purchases so that we can complete your order, including your name, shipping information, e-mail, phone number, and information about the products you purchase and your online order. Please be advised that we may send you e-mail alerts regarding the status of your purchases and/or to ask for your feedback. Links to the policies of our current Payment Processor, Shopify, are included in the section below entitled “DOES PHWC USE OTHER THIRD PARTY SERVICE PROVIDERS?”.
        p.section-heading#s7 DOES PHWC USE OTHER THIRD PARTY SERVICE PROVIDERS?
        p
          | We use the third party service provider Shopify Inc. (“
          strong Shopify
          | ”) to power our e-commerce platform. We encourage you to read Shopify’s policies if you intend to make purchases through our Site by clicking the following links:
        ul
          li
            | Shopify’s privacy policy: 
            a(href='https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy') https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy
          li
            | Shopify’s terms of service: 
            a(href='https://www.shopify.com/legal/terms') https://www.shopify.com/legal/terms
        p
          | In order to send you our newsletter and certain other communications, we use a third party service provider called MailChimp, which is owned and operated by The Rocket Science Group, LLC (“
          strong MailChimp
          | ”). MailChimp helps us build contact lists and prepare communications for distribution. Your name and email address may be seen and processed by MailChimp in order for us to utilize this tool. We encourage you to read MailChimp’s privacy policy and terms of use by clicking the following links:
        ul
          li
            | MailChimp’s privacy policy: 
            a(href='https://mailchimp.com/legal/privacy/') https://mailchimp.com/legal/privacy/
          li
            | MailChimp’s terms of use: 
            a(href='https://mailchimp.com/legal/terms/') https://mailchimp.com/legal/terms/
        p.section-heading#s8 CAN I CHOOSE TO STOP RECEIVING COMMUNICATIONS FROM PHWC?
        p
          | You can always choose to stop receiving newsletters or other electronic communications from us by clicking the “unsubscribe” link at the bottom of a PHWC message. Please understand that if you choose to unsubscribe from promotional correspondence from us, we may still contact you in connection with your relationship, activities, transactions and/or communications with us.
        p.section-heading#s9 CAN CHILDREN USE THE PHWC WEBSITE?
        p
          | We do not intentionally gather information from individuals who are under the age of 13. Upon notification that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete the child’s personal information from our records.
        p.section-heading#s10 WHAT IF I LIVE IN CALIFORNIA?
        p
          | California Civil Code Section 1798.83 permits Site visitors who are California residents and who have provided us with "personal information" (as that term is defined in Section 1798.83) to request certain information about the disclosure of that information to third parties for their direct marketing purposes. If you are a California resident, you may contact us by writing to: Perricone Hydrogen Water Company, LLC, 639 Research Parkway, Meriden, CT 06450.
        p.section-heading#s11 WHAT IF I LIVE OUTSIDE THE UNITED STATES?
        p
          | You should be aware that the United States and other countries have not harmonized their privacy regulations. Because PHWC and its servers are located in the United States and our services are directed towards the United States market, our Privacy Policy has been prepared to comply with applicable United States regulations. By accessing and/or using the Site or our services and providing personal information to us through the Site, you agree to the level of privacy protection set out in this Privacy Policy.
        p.section-heading#s12 WHAT IF I LIVE IN CANADA?
        p
          | Canadian citizens, except under circumstances defined by law, are entitled to access their own personal information collected by PHWC by writing to: Perricone Hydrogen Water Company, LLC, 639 Research Parkway, Meriden, CT 06450. If you believe that the personal information about you that we have collected is incomplete or inaccurate, please contact us and we will correct the information upon verification of the omission or error and of the identity of the person requesting the change.
        p.section-heading#s13 WHAT IF I FOLLOW A LINK TO A THIRD PARTY WEBSITE?
        p
          | The Site may contain links to other websites. The fact that we link to a website is not an endorsement, authorization or representation of our affiliation with that third party. We do not exercise control over third party websites. These other websites (including our Payment Processor) may place their own cookies or other files on your computer, collect data, or solicit personal information from you. Other sites follow different rules regarding the use or disclosure of the personal information you submit to them. We encourage you to read the privacy policies or statements of the other websites. Please be aware that the terms of our Privacy Policy do not apply to these third party websites.
        p.section-heading#s14 WILL PHWC CHANGE THIS PRIVACY POLICY?
        p
          | Each time you use the Site, the current version of this Privacy Policy will apply. When you use the Site, you should check the date of this Privacy Policy and review any changes since the last version. Visitors can always refuse to accept changes to our Privacy Policy by ending their use of the Site. Unless stated otherwise, our current Privacy Policy applies to all information that we have about you. Continuation of your use of the Site shall be considered acceptance of any changes in the Privacy Policy.
        p.section-heading#s15 HOW DO I CONTACT PHWC?
        p
          | If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, or you wish to update or request that we delete the information you have shared with us, you may contact us at 
